    "recap_headline": "Miami Ohio University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OXFORD, Ohio \u2013\nMiami defeated the Dayton Flyers Wednesday in a 13-7 contest after a seven-run second inning. Four different RedHawks had multiple hits during the game. Miami improves to 13-5 with the win while Dayton moves to 13-7 on the year.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nDayton turned two hits and a wild pitch into a run in the top of the second to break the 0-0 tie, taking a 1-1 lead.\nMason Breidenbach\nled off the second inning with a walk.\nMatthew Buffington\nfollowed with a base hit, sliding into second to make it a double. A ball-four wild pitch walked\nDiego Cruz\nand scored Breidenbach to make it 1-1 and force a pitching change.\nStill with no outs, Cruz stole second.\nMarcus Dierks\nwalked on a seven-pitch at bat to load the bases.\nRyan Novak\nput up a sacrifice fly to give the RedHawks the lead at 2-1.\nEvan Appelwick\nwalked to load the bases again and an error scored two runs. A single by\nIgnacio Gonzalez\nadded two more to make it 6-1.\nDominic Krupinski\ncontinued Miami's offensive push in the second with a ground-rule double to right-center.\u00a0 Breidenbach walked to load the bases yet another time and a passed ball promptly scored Miami's seventh run.\nWith one aboard, Buffington doubled to left center to put two runners in scoring position in the fourth. Cruz came up with a two-RBI double to extend the lead to 9-1.\nThe Flyers capitalized on three hits in the fifth, scoring four more runs.\nHarrison and Gonzalez put up back-to-back singles in the bottom of the fifth. Krupinski doubled to score them both and make it an 11-5 game.\nMiami added two more runs in the sixth. Cruz and Dierks each walked and stole a bag and Cruz advanced to score on an error. An RBI groundout scored Dierks to make it 13-5.\nDayton cut the deficit to six runs, scoring twice in the top of the seventh.\nThe RedHawks held the Flyers scoreless for the final two innings, securing a 13-7 victory.\nMIAMI GAME NOTES:\nDierks went 1-for-3 with two runs and three walks.\nHarrison went 2-for-4 with two runs and an RBI.\nGonzalez went 2-for-3 with two runs and two RBIs.\nKrupinski went 2-for-5 with two RBIs.\nBreidenbach went 1-for-3 with two runs and two walks.\nBuffington went 2-for-5 with two runs and two doubles.\nCruz went 1-for-3 with two runs and two RBIs.\nUP NEXT:\nThe RedHawks will travel to Northern Illinois this weekend for a three-game series. Game one is scheduled for Friday, March 20 at 4 p.m."
